sentence.text: Homozygous null mutation of tumor suppressor WWOX/negative regulation of Wnt signaling pathway gene leads to severe neural diseases, metabolic disorders and early death in the newborns of humans, epidermis development and rats.

entity.text: negative regulation of Wnt signaling pathway

sentence.text: In vitro analysis revealed that knockdown of negative regulation of Wnt signaling pathway protein in neuroblastoma cells results in aggregation of TRAPPC6AΔ, I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB signaling, amyloid β, and microtubule cytoskeleton organization in a sequential manner.
